SIMPLE: warlike
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warlike
<hw>War"like`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fit for
war; disposed for war; <as>as, a <ex>warlike</ex> state; a
<ex>warlike</ex> disposition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old Siward, with ten thousand <qex>warlike</qex> men.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Belonging or relating to war; military;
martial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The great archangel from his <qex>warlike</qex> toil
Surceased.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Martial; hostile; soldierly. See
<er>Martial</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warlikeness</ent>⟦br⟧
